Real Madrid has appointed Antonio Pintus as the club’s fitness manager. The LaLiga giants made the announcement in a statement via their website on Friday. Pintus’s appointment is coming less than three days after Real Madrid appointed Carlo Ancelotti as the club’s manager on Tuesday Ancelotti replaced Zinedine Zidane, who stepped down from his role last month. The statement read, “Real Madrid C. F. announce the incorporation of Antonio Pintus as first-team head of physical preparation and physical preparation methodology manager for all the football teams at the club.” Meanwhile, Real Madrid finished the 2020/21 LaLiga season in the second position behind champions Atletico Madrid. The Los Blancos were also knocked out of the Champions League in the semi-final stage by champions Chelsea. Chelsea vs West Brom: Pulisic gives fitness update ahead of EPL clash